---
// Problem.astro
---

<section class="problem section section-light">
  <div class="container problem-container">
    <h2>For millions of children, the rules of language are invisible.</h2>
    <div class="problem-body">
      <p>
        Grammar is the connective tissue between learning vocabulary and
        achieving true literacy. It is critical to reading comprehension,
        academic achievement, and everyday life skills. Without it,
        communication remains a collection of isolated labels.
      </p>
      <p>
        For children with complex communication needs — including autism,
        developmental language disorder (DLD), and dyslexia — these essential
        rules don't come effortlessly. The patterns remain invisible, making
        traditional abstract workbooks ineffective. By making the structure of
        language visually explicit, we can unlock their ability to build
        sentences, comprehend texts, and communicate their thoughts clearly.
      </p>
      <p class="highlight">
        What if grammar wasn't invisible? What if a child could <em>see</em> it?
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    padding: var(--spacing-24) 0;
  }

  .problem-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-8);
  }

  .problem-body p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .problem-body .highlight {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent-orange);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-6);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
